Initialization now is working on both `Sanic` and `Blueprint`. See #63 for previous note about the difficulty. I am not yet 100% thrilled with the solution. However, it is certainly good enough for now to get us over the next hump.

In order to accomplish the addition of protecting on a `Blueprint`, added it as a parameter to `@protected`. It also needs to be added (still) to `@scoped`.

```python
blueprint = Blueprint('Test')

@blueprint.get("/")
@protected(blueprint)
def hello_world(request):
    return json({'message': 'hello world'})
```

I have some other ideas that in the future I want to experiment with (attaching the `Initialize` instance to the `request`, or making the decorators methods on `Initialize`), but no need to tackle them now since they would require some changes inside of the `Initialize` class.

More important now, I think, is for me to finish up with a few more tests and to get these API changes into the new docs.

