@hmaarrfk Rudimentary typing of NumPy arrays can already be achieved with the following:

```python
import typing as typ
import numpy as np

DType = typ.TypeVar('DType')

class Array(np.ndarray, typ.MutableSequence[DType], extra=np.ndarray):
    
    __slots__ = ()
    
    def __new__(cls, *args, **kwds):
        if cls._gorg is Array:
            raise TypeError("Type Array cannot be instantiated; "
                            "use np.array() instead.")
        return typ._generic_new(np.ndarray, cls, *args, *kwds)
```

I'll need to look some more through the [typing source code](https://github.com/python/typing/blob/master/src/typing.py) to get an idea of how we can pass `array.dtype`, complete checking against a definition of `array_like` instead of `np.ndarray`, and automatic conversion to NumPy arrays (this won't be possible yet until the PSF actually decides to enforce types itself).

For the proposed API of shape-specification, see https://github.com/Napari/napari/issues/1#issuecomment-395392463.

