@daspecster I think this is because `json_payload` is not defined in the [proto](https://github.com/googleapis/googleapis/blob/master/google/logging/v2/log_entry.proto#L67) as `map<string, string>` like `labels` is. Instead it is defined as [`google.protobuf.Struct`](https://github.com/google/protobuf/blob/master/src/google/protobuf/struct.proto#L52), which adds one more level to the object hierarchy.

Change [this code](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python/blob/0aca3f6ed05f3340333f231445a3d8b17d8d8e6c/logging/google/cloud/logging/_gax.py#L605):

```python
    if 'jsonPayload' in mapping:
        for key, value in mapping['jsonPayload'].items():
            entry_pb.json_payload[key] = value
```

To something like:

```python
    if 'jsonPayload' in mapping:
        fields = {}
        for key, value in mapping['jsonPayload'].items():
            fields[key] = value
        entry_pb.json_payload = google.protobuf.Struct(fields)
```

